    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA249-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiviṭai melintatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what [expresses] a weakened [state] during the time to the marriage.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA249">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            irumpi ṉaṉṉa karuṅkōṭṭup puṉṉai</l>
<l>            nīlat taṉṉa pācilai yakantoṟum</l>
<l>            veḷḷi yaṉṉa viḷaṅkiṇar nāppaṭ</l>
<l>            poṉṉi ṉaṉṉa naṟuntā tutirap</l>
<l>            pulippoṟik koṇṭa pūnāṟu kurūuccuval </l>
<l>            varivaṇ ṭūtaliṟ pulicettu verīip</l>
<l>            pariyuṭai vayaṅkutāḷ pantiṟ ṟāvat</l>
<l>            tāṅkavun takaivarai nillā vāṅkaṇ</l>
<l>            mallalañ cēri kalleṉat tōṉṟiya</l>
<l>            yampaṉ mūtū ralareḻac </l>
<l>            ceṉṟa taṉṟō koṇkaṉ ṟērē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The chariot of the man from the sea, hasn’t it gone</l>
<l rend="indent">so that gossip rises in this talkative old village,</l>
<l>[the chariot] which appeared<note place="foot">Here the variants <term xml:lang="ta">tōṉṟiya</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">tōṉṟi</term> both have to be connected with <term xml:lang="ta">tēr</term> (because the preceding absolutive <term xml:lang="ta">nillā</term> has to refer to the chariot), although <term xml:lang="ta">tōṉṟiya</term> would more easily construe with alar as subject.</note> noisily in the wealthy pretty quarter</l>
<l>there without standing still although he stopped,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the swift gleaming legs<note place="foot">These legs without doubt belong to the horses yoked to HIS chariot, but they are elliptical here.</note> were leaping like balls,</l>
<l rend="indent2">frightened<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">verīi</term>: we would rather have a <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> here.</note>, thinking [them] tigers, of the striped bees filling</l>
<l rend="indent2">themselves up on the brilliant height fragrant with flowers</l>
<l rend="indent3">that took the dots of the tiger,</l>
<l rend="indent">while fragrant pollen drops off like gold</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the centre of the clusters shining like silver</l>
<l rend="indent2">in every inside [surrounded by?] leaves green like blue lotus</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the Puṉṉai tree with branches black like iron?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
